organic_results.title: Socioeconomic status as related to aptitude, attrition, and achievement of college students
organic_results.snippet: Black college students from three socioeconomic levels were compared on the following variables: SAT scores (verbal and math); attrition two years after matriculation; grade point average (GPA) at the end of the first college semester and after two years; correlation (r) between SAT-V and first semester GPA within each socioeconomic group. The expectation of a positive relationship between socioeconomic status (SES) and SAT scores was only partially confirmed. SAT-V predicted GPA for lower SES students as well as for higher SES …
